parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to drop to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal drops to the floor
brake fluid leaks
corrosion on brake lines
and increased stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: ABS system engages at low speeds
ABS system does not disengage
increased stopping distance
and vibration or shaking of the vehicle when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to drop to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal drops to the floor
brake fluid leaks
and corrosion on brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during heavy rain or stormy conditions.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working or work intermittently
sometimes requiring manual intervention to restart
such as tapping on the wiper module or waiting for a few minutes before they start working again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the windows to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windows do not stay on track when rolling up or down
requiring manual intervention to correct.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto-dimming rear view mirror can cause glare from the rear window, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Auto-dimming feature fails to dim the rear view mirror
requiring manual intervention to adjust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to suddenly jerk or veer to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels heavy or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel jerks or skips during turns
the vehicle wanders at highway speeds
the brakes fail at panic stops
and the pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering sensor can cause the power steering system to malfunction, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels heavy or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel jerks or skips during turns
the power steering system binds momentarily
and then full power assist occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control or veer unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel jerks or skips during turns
and the vehicle wanders at highway speeds.
